Subject: [PATCH] doc: test: add documentation for twister sysbuild flag

Add sysbuild flag to twister supported options, with documentation on
how Kconfig and devicetree will be parsed

Signed-off-by: Daniel DeGrasse <daniel.degrasse@nxp.com>
---
 doc/develop/test/twister.rst | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/doc/develop/test/twister.rst b/doc/develop/test/twister.rst
index 91aa166314..5e6aa605b2 100644
--- a/doc/develop/test/twister.rst
+++ b/doc/develop/test/twister.rst
@@ -362,6 +362,12 @@ harness_config: <harness configuration options>
     ordered: <True|False> (default False)
         Check the regular expression strings in orderly or randomly fashion
 
+    sysbuild: <True|False> (default False)
+        Build the project using sysbuild infrastructure. Only the main project's
+        generated devicetree and Kconfig will be used for filtering tests.
+        on device testing must use the hardware map, or west flash to load
+        the images onto the target.
+
     repeat: <integer>
         Number of times to validate the repeated regex expression
 
